    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="293"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José, Costa Rica</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1152.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise the election as
                    President of Costa Rica of Señor Cleto Gonzales Viquez by the electoral college
                    which convened at the seven capitals of the departments on the 1st instant.</p>
                <p>The new Executive will be inaugurated on May 8, for a four years’ term. Señor
                    Gonzales is 51 years old, born in the neighboring Province of Heredia, and a
                    lawyer of good reputation, with considerable ability. He was at one time
                    minister of fomento (public works), president of the municipal council of the
                    city and Province of San Jose, and president of the College of Law at San Jose.
                    He has traveled abroad considerably and speaks English fairly well.</p>
                <p>With assurances of my highest consideration, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Lawrence Merry.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
